Paper: hep-th/9905156

Date: 1999-05-21

Title: Supersymmetry and generalized calibrations

Authors: J. Gutowski, G. Papadopoulos and P.K. Townsend

Comments: Revtex. 11 pp. Minor corrections made and references added. To appear

in Phys. Rev. DJournal-ref: Phys.Rev. D60 (1999) 106006

A static minimal energy configuration of a super p-brane in a supersymmetric(n+1)-dimensional spacetime is shown to be a `generalized calibrated'submanifold. Calibrations in $\bE^{(1,n)}$ and $AdS_{n+1}$ are special cases.We present several M-brane examples.